y=\frac{x}{2}-\frac{x^2}{16}
y=\frac x2-\frac{x^2}{16}\Longleftrightarrow x^2-8x=-16y\Longleftrightarrow(x-4)^2-16=-16y\Longleftrightarrow(x-4)^2=16(1-y)
y\leq1
x\geq4
x=4+4\sqrt{1-y}
x\leq4
x=4-4\sqrt{1-y}.
\dfrac{1}{16}x^2-\dfrac{1}{2}x+y=0\\ \implies \boxed{x=4\left(1\pm\sqrt{1-y}\right)}
y\leq1
